<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<p class="meta">
<strong>Game:</strong> Myrix Tap My Colour<br>
<strong>Developer:</strong> Myrix Games<br>
<strong>Effective Date:</strong> 13 March 2026<br>
<strong>Last Updated:</strong> 13 March 2026
</p>


<h2>1. Introduction</h2>

<p>
Myrix Games ("we", "our", or "us") operates the game <strong>Myrix Tap My Colour</strong> (the “Game”).
</p>

<p>
This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when users play the Game on supported platforms including web browsers, Reddit, or mobile devices.
</p>

<p>
By using the Game, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
</p>


<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

<h3>a) Personal Information</h3>

<p>
The Game does <strong>not require users to create accounts</strong> or provide personally identifiable information such as:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Full name</li>
<li>Email address</li>
<li>Phone number</li>
<li>Address</li>
<li>Contacts</li>
<li>Precise location</li>
</ul>


<h3>b) Nicknames Submitted by Players</h3>

<p>
Players may optionally submit a nickname when recording a score on the global leaderboard.
</p>

<ul>
<li>The nickname is chosen by the player</li>
<li>It may be displayed publicly on the leaderboard</li>
<li>It is limited to short non-identifying text</li>
<li>Special characters may be filtered automatically</li>
</ul>

<p>
Players are advised not to use real names or personal information as nicknames.
</p>


<h3>c) Gameplay Data</h3>

<p>
The Game may store limited gameplay information including:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Score</li>
<li>Game mode (Timed or Infinite)</li>
<li>Time of score submission</li>
</ul>

<p>
This information is used only to support gameplay features such as leaderboards.
</p>


<h3>d) Local Storage</h3>

<p>
The Game may store certain information locally on the user's device, including:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Saved nickname</li>
<li>Sound settings</li>
<li>Tutorial preferences</li>
<li>Gameplay configuration</li>
</ul>

<p>
This data is stored only on the user's device and is not transmitted unless a player submits a score.
</p>


<h2>3. Leaderboards</h2>

<p>
If a player submits a score, the following information may be stored on a leaderboard service:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Nickname</li>
<li>Score</li>
<li>Game mode</li>
<li>Timestamp of submission</li>
</ul>

<p>
Leaderboard information may be displayed publicly within the Game.
</p>

<p>
No personal identity information is required or stored.
</p>


<h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>

<p>
The Game may use third-party services to support certain features including:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Backend leaderboard databases</li>
<li>Hosting platforms</li>
<li>Platform services such as Reddit</li>
</ul>

<p>
These services operate under their own privacy policies and data practices.
</p>


<h2>5. Advertising (Future Versions)</h2>

<p>
Future versions of <strong>Myrix Tap My Colour</strong> may include advertising services such as Google AdMob.
</p>

<p>
Advertising providers may collect certain information including:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Device information</li>
<li>Advertising identifiers</li>
<li>IP address</li>
<li>Interaction data</li>
</ul>

<p>
Google Privacy Policy:
<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">
https://policies.google.com/privacy
</a>
</p>


<h2>6. Analytics</h2>

<p>
The Game does not currently use analytics services.
</p>

<p>
If analytics tools are introduced in future updates, this Privacy Policy will be updated accordingly.
</p>


<h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>

<p>
The Game is suitable for general audiences.
</p>

<p>
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.
</p>

<p>
If you believe personal information has been submitted by a child, please contact us and we will remove it.
</p>


<h2>8. Data Security</h2>

<p>
We take reasonable measures to protect stored data.
</p>

<p>
Leaderboard data contains only gameplay information such as scores and nicknames.
</p>


<h2>9. Future Features and Services</h2>

<p>
Future updates of the Game may introduce additional features including but not limited to:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Online leaderboards</li>
<li>Cloud save systems</li>
<li>Analytics services</li>
<li>Advertising services</li>
<li>Multiplayer features</li>
<li>Account systems</li>
</ul>

<p>
If such features are introduced, they may require limited gameplay or device information necessary for those features to function.
</p>

<p>
Any such additions will comply with platform policies and privacy regulations.
</p>


<h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>

<p>
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically.
</p>

<p>
Updates will be posted on this page with a revised “Last Updated” date.
</p>


